Why Git?

1. Tracking

- track changes and version history
- see who did what, keeps people honest
- can go back to a previous version easily, say if you break your code

2. Public Record

- show your code to employers as a resume builder, proof that you can code
- helps with reproducibility, other people can run your code and reproduce
your results

3. Sharing is Caring

- don't need to reinvent the wheel every time someone does a similar analysis
- easier collaboration and sharing of resources
- ReadMes are great for explaining your code and how it works